aiResponses.question_33402666002:
Thank you for prioritizing an accessible and inclusive interview experience. I do not require any ongoing accommodations for interviews by default, and I am comfortable participating via video conferencing (Zoom, Google Meet) or by phone. I work on Central Time (UTC-6/UTC-5 as applicable) and am available for interviews on weekdays between 9:00 AM and 4:00 PM CT; if needed I can occasionally make myself available earlier or later with advance notice.

When helpful, I appreciate having an agenda and any technical instructions in writing ahead of time (e.g., systems to access, repos or sample code to review). In prior roles at TechCorp and StartupXYZ I collaborated with globally distributed teams across the US and EMEA; providing written prompts or sample artifacts in advance improved the efficiency and fairness of technical discussions. If any live coding exercises are required, I am happy to do them in a shared document or in an environment where a copy of the prompt is available in text form.

If additional accommodations become necessary at any stage (for example, preference for closed captions, transcripts of recorded sessions, or extended time for a take-home assignment), I will request them promptly. I value GitLab's emphasis on accessibility and collaboration and am committed to working with your team to ensure a smooth, inclusive process for everyone involved.
